oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: P. L. Fite Produce Company
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of P. L. Fite Produce Company building. There is a sign covering the side of the building that says "I smoke for pleasure, I'd walk a mile for a Camel." Prentice L. Fite (1898-1980) was the owner of the company.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Farm produce; Stores & shops; Advertisements
